<br>
No official list need be made I think.  People make up their minds about things and if important enough you'll remember.  I suspect there is a search function here as well if you want to check someone out.  The flames stand on their merit for each reader to decide if the flamee was justly or unjustly flamed.<br>
<br>
If someone is accused people can view the whole exchange, and using Fablaar thread as an example, can see the eventual outcome and make up their own minds.<br>
<br>
Official black ball lists usually lose their effectiveness due to abuse.  There rarely exists a mechanism for getting off of such a list as well.<br>
<br>
Of course it would be painful if someone started listing all the times someone has their alt trained in DS at NL zone because someone is not bright enough to avoid the mushrooms along the way from ME and unwilling to kill them after picking them up.  But the more eggregious (sp?) things get listed and I suspect people pay attention if it's important to them.<br>
<br>
Or so it seems to me<br>
